WEBVTT

00:00:18.460 --> 00:00:21.530
You're certainly up and running early.

00:00:21.530 --> 00:00:22.530
Well, yeah.

00:00:23.050 --> 00:00:25.850
I need to start looking good again soon.

00:00:25.850 --> 00:00:28.430
Have you decided on a return race?

00:00:28.430 --> 00:00:29.690
The Takarazuka Kinen.

00:00:30.320 --> 00:00:32.000
I'm gonna win this time.

00:00:32.000 --> 00:00:35.530
It'll be my pleasure to 
shatter that confidence.

00:00:36.910 --> 00:00:39.160
I'll be going on ahead, then.

00:00:41.060 --> 00:00:43.540
I just said I was going to go on ahead!

00:00:44.460 --> 00:00:45.760
Honestly...

00:00:45.760 --> 00:00:49.670
Teio-sama certainly seems 
to enjoy her running.

00:00:51.470 --> 00:00:54.380
That's just who she is.

00:01:11.480 --> 00:01:18.740
Umamusume

00:01:14.690 --> 00:01:18.740
Pretty Derby

00:02:25.580 --> 00:02:30.540
{\an1}Episode 9
 Stopwatch

00:02:30.540 --> 00:02:33.520
Very nice. That was your best time yet.

00:02:33.840 --> 00:02:36.640
Really?! Time for another one, then!

00:02:36.640 --> 00:02:39.060
Whoa. You sure you're not overdoing it?

00:02:39.060 --> 00:02:42.410
Can't help it! I just wanna run so bad!

00:02:42.410 --> 00:02:45.040
Looks like our ex-leader is really fired up.

00:02:45.040 --> 00:02:47.470
And here I thought I was 
gonna be leader next.

00:02:47.470 --> 00:02:49.290
Vodka, Scarlet...

00:02:49.290 --> 00:02:52.540
I am the leader

00:02:49.930 --> 00:02:52.220
It's me, your new leader... Golshi-chan.

00:02:57.800 --> 00:03:00.220
Someone else is feeling motivated, too.

00:03:03.720 --> 00:03:05.930
Okay, here I go!

00:03:05.930 --> 00:03:06.920
Ready?

00:03:07.360 --> 00:03:08.180
Go!

00:03:14.590 --> 00:03:18.270
I can finally... finally race with McQueen!

00:03:19.080 --> 00:03:21.320
The Classics series is upon us!

00:03:21.770 --> 00:03:23.660
This season, it looks like 
a lot of attention will be

00:03:23.660 --> 00:03:25.630
focused on Satsuki winner Narita Taishin!

00:03:25.630 --> 00:03:27.500
Hey, Rice!

00:03:25.630 --> 00:03:29.080
There's also Winning Ticket, who's shown
a remarkable focus on the Derby.

00:03:27.870 --> 00:03:29.080
Teio-san?

00:03:29.080 --> 00:03:30.280
Care for one?

00:03:29.080 --> 00:03:36.420
Team
Mimosa
Recruiting Members!!

00:03:29.560 --> 00:03:33.300
And one can hardly ignore the 
looming presence of Biwa Hayahide!

00:03:30.280 --> 00:03:32.330
Oh, I bet you don't eat bread, though!

00:03:32.330 --> 00:03:35.580
Actually, I do, with breakfast.

00:03:33.300 --> 00:03:38.140
The three of them are shaping up to be the 
new heroines of this season of racing!

00:03:35.580 --> 00:03:36.420
I see.

00:03:36.420 --> 00:03:40.120
Congrats again on the Tennoushou. 
You were really amazing!

00:03:38.730 --> 00:03:44.230
So much that I'm sure I don't 
have to tell you they've

00:03:40.500 --> 00:03:42.080
Thank you...

00:03:42.080 --> 00:03:44.890
But I'm gonna avenge McQueen.

00:03:44.890 --> 00:03:47.250
So be ready to race me some day!

00:03:44.890 --> 00:03:48.300
become collectively known as BNW.

00:03:47.250 --> 00:03:48.300
See ya!

00:03:49.140 --> 00:03:54.400
And for today's program, I want to 
get up close and personal with BNW!

00:03:50.280 --> 00:03:53.660
We've... already raced before, though.

00:03:54.400 --> 00:03:56.770
The horse girls are steadily making 
their way around the track,

00:03:56.990 --> 00:03:59.780
and Narita Taishin is 
currently in third place,

00:03:59.780 --> 00:04:01.300
with two competitors in front of her.

00:04:01.300 --> 00:04:02.780
We're down to the last 400 meters now.

00:04:02.780 --> 00:04:04.580
And Winning Ticket is moving up!

00:04:04.580 --> 00:04:06.490
Right behind her is Biwa Hayahide!

00:04:06.490 --> 00:04:07.780
Narita Taishin has joined them!

00:04:08.030 --> 00:04:10.790
And it looks like BNW has 
collectively made their move!

00:04:10.790 --> 00:04:13.710
The Derby! The Derby I've 
always dreamed about!

00:04:14.030 --> 00:04:16.790
I may have lost the Satsukishou, 
but this is where I win!

00:04:17.110 --> 00:04:19.680
I can do this! I can come out on top!

00:04:28.050 --> 00:04:29.460
Winning Ticket in the lead!

00:04:29.460 --> 00:04:31.280
And Winning Ticket finishes first!

00:04:30.490 --> 00:04:31.810
Japanese Derby

00:04:31.280 --> 00:04:34.430
Biwa Hayahide and Narita Taishin 
in second and third place!

00:04:34.430 --> 00:04:36.810
It looks like BNW are just too strong!

00:04:36.810 --> 00:04:39.820
The Derby goes to Winning Ticket!

00:04:37.970 --> 00:04:43.070
Ticket! Ticket! Ticket!

00:04:43.070 --> 00:04:53.330
Ticket! Ticket! Ticket!

00:04:53.330 --> 00:04:55.590
W-Wow...

00:04:55.590 --> 00:04:58.210
The race was practically 
between the three of them.

00:04:58.210 --> 00:05:00.210
We've got some more tough competition.

00:05:00.430 --> 00:05:02.960
So they're BNW.

00:05:02.960 --> 00:05:05.050
They're BNW?!

00:05:05.050 --> 00:05:06.770
Not too bad!

00:05:06.770 --> 00:05:09.300
They truly seem to
posses incredible talent.

00:05:09.680 --> 00:05:11.570
But so do we.

00:05:13.810 --> 00:05:15.010
I did it!

00:05:15.010 --> 00:05:18.480
Ikuno Dictus comes in second 
place at the Yasuda Kinen!

00:05:22.070 --> 00:05:23.940
Ikuno Dictus

00:05:22.440 --> 00:05:23.940
Congrats, Ikuno!

00:05:24.160 --> 00:05:26.350
I would have preferred to have won, but...

00:05:26.350 --> 00:05:29.310
A second place finish in 
the G1 is still awesome!

00:05:29.310 --> 00:05:30.950
Is your next race set already?

00:05:31.230 --> 00:05:32.650
The Takarazuka Kinen.

00:05:32.650 --> 00:05:34.720
Next time, you're gonna win a G1 race!

00:05:34.720 --> 00:05:36.710
Yes. I intend to make up for this loss.

00:05:36.930 --> 00:05:41.330
I've heard Mejiro McQueen and Tokai Teio 
will be running in the Takarazuka Kinen.

00:05:41.330 --> 00:05:43.290
Teio's finally making her return.

00:05:43.290 --> 00:05:45.510
Well, duh! This is Teio we're talking about!

00:05:45.510 --> 00:05:47.220
Why are <i>you</i> acting so proud?

00:05:47.220 --> 00:05:49.380
This time we're gonna beat Spica!

00:05:49.380 --> 00:05:50.310
Right!

00:05:50.310 --> 00:05:52.270
Me too! I wanna race, too!

00:05:52.270 --> 00:05:56.230
The next race you're eligible for, 
Turbo-san, is the Tanabata Sho.

00:05:56.230 --> 00:05:57.690
Is that in the G1?

00:05:57.690 --> 00:05:59.100
It's in the G3.

00:06:04.180 --> 00:06:06.610
That smells nice.

00:06:06.610 --> 00:06:08.220
Ow!

00:06:09.610 --> 00:06:11.330
Good day, Palmer.

00:06:12.120 --> 00:06:14.490
Hey, McQueen. What's up?

00:06:14.490 --> 00:06:16.390
I never see you around this part of campus.

00:06:16.390 --> 00:06:19.730
I'm just here for a change of clothes. 
Then I'll be on my way back to the dorms.

00:06:19.730 --> 00:06:23.120
Is something going on with you?
 Your nose is very red.

00:06:23.120 --> 00:06:24.630
Uh, it's nothing!

00:06:24.630 --> 00:06:26.130
I see.

00:06:26.130 --> 00:06:29.300
I'm afraid I can't allow you to 
win a second Takarazuka Kinen.

00:06:29.300 --> 00:06:32.390
Well, I'm not giving up without a fight!

00:06:32.390 --> 00:06:34.520
I'm looking forward to it.

00:06:34.520 --> 00:06:36.140
If you'll excuse me.

00:06:37.540 --> 00:06:39.020
I'm gonna ultim-outrun her!

00:06:39.390 --> 00:06:41.980
Two years ago, it was Mejiro Ryan.

00:06:41.980 --> 00:06:44.220
Last year, it was Mejiro Palmer.

00:06:44.220 --> 00:06:48.280
This time, I will be winning.

00:06:49.820 --> 00:06:52.030
Another long day!

00:06:52.030 --> 00:06:54.840
But I've gotta stay on my toes!

00:06:54.840 --> 00:06:56.350
Okay, let's do this!

00:06:56.350 --> 00:06:57.040
Teio...

00:07:00.630 --> 00:07:02.640
P-Prez...

00:07:07.550 --> 00:07:09.050
How are you feeling?

00:07:09.050 --> 00:07:11.670
Uh... I'm sorry!

00:07:12.050 --> 00:07:13.580
Why are you apologizing?

00:07:13.580 --> 00:07:17.010
Well... I've been avoiding you, Prez.

00:07:17.010 --> 00:07:18.390
I noticed.

00:07:19.320 --> 00:07:20.520
I guess so.

00:07:22.030 --> 00:07:26.380
I wasn't sure why I was running.

00:07:26.380 --> 00:07:28.060
And I was so anxious.

00:07:28.690 --> 00:07:32.320
I didn't want you to see me
 when I was like that.

00:07:32.360 --> 00:07:34.320
Aim to be an undefeated Triple Crown horse girl!

00:07:32.860 --> 00:07:34.320
I felt guilty.

00:07:36.610 --> 00:07:37.820
I see.

00:07:37.820 --> 00:07:38.930
Yeah.

00:07:38.930 --> 00:07:44.660
But now I have someone who I want 
to look good for as much as you!

00:07:46.100 --> 00:07:48.330
As much as me, eh?

00:07:48.710 --> 00:07:50.150
Are you jealous?

00:07:51.490 --> 00:07:53.520
This is your first race 
in six months, isn't it?

00:07:53.520 --> 00:07:56.380
Yeah. I'm gonna make sure it's a good one.

00:07:57.260 --> 00:08:01.440
I want everyone to see, "This is Tokai Teio!"

00:08:01.440 --> 00:08:03.890
Maybe then, instead of chasing you,

00:08:03.890 --> 00:08:06.980
I can be the kind of horse girl who 
can stand next to you as an equal.

00:08:06.980 --> 00:08:10.400
And then one day, maybe even surpass you.

00:08:10.940 --> 00:08:14.630
So the Takarazuka Kinen is going 
to my first step towards that.

00:08:14.630 --> 00:08:15.820
Teio...

00:08:16.050 --> 00:08:19.770
So be sure to watch me run, Prez!

00:08:20.500 --> 00:08:22.780
Right, I'll be looking forward to it.

00:08:28.400 --> 00:08:29.990
Back in action, huh?

00:08:30.340 --> 00:08:32.770
I'd expect nothing less of Tokai Teio!

00:08:32.770 --> 00:08:35.200
Of course I'm back, Double Turbo.

00:08:35.200 --> 00:08:36.970
It's Twin Turbo! Quit getting it wrong!

00:08:37.540 --> 00:08:38.830
Sorry, sorry!

00:08:38.830 --> 00:08:41.270
So did you need something?

00:08:41.270 --> 00:08:44.560
I just wanted to let you know 
I'm gonna win the Tanabata Sho!

00:08:44.560 --> 00:08:45.550
Okay...

00:08:45.550 --> 00:08:48.080
And then I'm gonna come challenge you!

00:08:48.560 --> 00:08:50.490
So next time, we're gonna race!

00:08:50.490 --> 00:08:51.970
Sure, okay.

00:08:52.960 --> 00:08:53.920
Next time, then.

00:08:55.470 --> 00:08:57.910
Yeah! It's a promise!

00:08:58.410 --> 00:09:00.590
What are you doing, Turbo-san?

00:09:00.590 --> 00:09:01.460
Ikuno?!

00:09:01.460 --> 00:09:03.450
You can't be bothering Teio-san.

00:09:03.450 --> 00:09:04.960
I'm not bothering her!

00:09:05.370 --> 00:09:06.980
Come along, now.

00:09:06.270 --> 00:09:08.820
Let me go!

00:09:06.980 --> 00:09:09.680
Sorry about that. She doesn't 
mean to cause any trouble.

00:09:08.820 --> 00:09:14.360
Ikuno, how are you even doing this?!

00:09:09.680 --> 00:09:11.790
She's just got brain problems.

00:09:11.790 --> 00:09:13.210
See ya!

00:09:14.990 --> 00:09:16.840
I wasn't done talking!

00:09:14.990 --> 00:09:18.220
Okay, let's do this!

00:09:16.840 --> 00:09:18.220
Let go!

00:09:28.150 --> 00:09:29.520
There we go.

00:09:29.980 --> 00:09:33.730
<font color="#45443d" size="22">Win against McQueen at the Takarazuka Kinen!</font>

00:09:42.180 --> 00:09:43.240
Well?

00:09:43.240 --> 00:09:45.050
You're definitely making progress.

00:09:45.050 --> 00:09:46.120
Keep it up!

00:09:49.100 --> 00:09:51.130
Oh, damn!

00:09:52.850 --> 00:09:55.130
I'm gonna go again, Trainer!

00:09:55.130 --> 00:09:56.870
All right, go for it!

00:10:00.640 --> 00:10:01.760
Okay.

00:10:02.390 --> 00:10:03.890
Ready...

00:10:03.890 --> 00:10:04.800
Go!

00:10:06.810 --> 00:10:07.940
Awesome!

00:10:07.940 --> 00:10:08.520
Yeah!

00:10:16.280 --> 00:10:17.830
My legs feel so light.

00:10:18.530 --> 00:10:21.030
My whole body wants to move forward!

00:10:34.050 --> 00:10:37.900
No matter how many times I fall,
 I can always dream again!

00:10:39.150 --> 00:10:41.970
And this time it's about 
my race with McQueen!

00:10:44.230 --> 00:10:45.510
I want to make sure to win—

00:11:12.060 --> 00:11:13.000
Teio!

00:11:13.000 --> 00:11:17.000
Umamusume

00:11:13.000 --> 00:11:17.000
{\an2}Pretty Derby

00:11:19.510 --> 00:11:20.970
It's a fracture.

00:11:22.540 --> 00:11:23.970
I see.

00:11:25.330 --> 00:11:29.170
Sorry, McQueen. I'm starting 
over from the beginning again.

00:11:29.880 --> 00:11:32.790
So when will I be able to race?

00:11:32.790 --> 00:11:34.940
This is your third fracture.

00:11:34.940 --> 00:11:36.770
There's a chance it's become recurrent.

00:11:37.900 --> 00:11:39.780
The fracture itself should heal,

00:11:39.780 --> 00:11:43.700
but it's hard to say whether you'll ever 
be able to run in the same fashion again.

00:11:44.430 --> 00:11:46.950
You've got about a 70% chance of recovery.

00:11:48.370 --> 00:11:53.920
It's unfortunate, but continuing 
to race is something I can't—

00:11:53.920 --> 00:11:55.330
It's okay, seriously!

00:11:55.330 --> 00:11:59.420
I'll heal! I've done it plenty before, right?

00:11:59.420 --> 00:12:00.460
Teio...

00:12:00.460 --> 00:12:02.840
Come on, quit it with that look!

00:12:02.840 --> 00:12:05.590
I'm gonna run again! I know it!

00:12:05.590 --> 00:12:07.780
It'll be just fine!

00:12:15.950 --> 00:12:19.320
I guess my race against McQueen at 
the Takarazuka Kinen is on hold.

00:12:19.320 --> 00:12:21.610
I was really looking forward to it, too.

00:12:22.750 --> 00:12:24.280
Teio, listen...

00:12:24.280 --> 00:12:26.730
I'm counting on you for another 
recovery regimen, Trainer.

00:12:27.150 --> 00:12:28.040
Sorry.

00:12:28.500 --> 00:12:32.000
What're you apologizing for? I'm fine.

00:12:32.700 --> 00:12:33.860
I mean it.

00:12:40.000 --> 00:12:42.260
BREAKING

00:12:40.000 --> 00:12:42.260
TOKAI TEIO

00:12:40.000 --> 00:12:42.260
THIRD FRACTURE

00:12:45.550 --> 00:12:47.800
Takarazuka Kinen

00:12:45.550 --> 00:12:47.800
Hanshin Racecourse

00:12:47.800 --> 00:12:49.160
It's gonna be hard for her to make a comeback...

00:12:49.160 --> 00:12:50.810
Thank you for everything

00:12:50.680 --> 00:12:52.350
Get all the rest that you need

00:12:52.270 --> 00:12:53.810
Thank you for the memories,
 Tokai Teio

