00:13:03.230 --> 00:13:04.570
Kita-chan...

00:13:05.270 --> 00:13:07.360
Teio-san will be okay.

00:13:16.580 --> 00:13:18.830
BREAKING

00:13:16.580 --> 00:13:18.830
TOKAI TEIO

00:13:16.580 --> 00:13:18.830
THIRD FRACTURE

00:13:26.590 --> 00:13:27.930
Teio...

00:13:27.930 --> 00:13:29.660
Teio will be back!

00:13:30.100 --> 00:13:32.310
I know she will!

00:13:32.310 --> 00:13:34.140
Because she's Tokai Teio!

00:13:36.170 --> 00:13:37.400
Turbo...

00:13:37.400 --> 00:13:40.370
Is there anything we can do for her?

00:13:40.370 --> 00:13:41.630
Give her a watermelon!

00:13:41.630 --> 00:13:44.110
Gifts, then? Anything else?

00:13:44.110 --> 00:13:45.610
Write her a letter!

00:13:45.610 --> 00:13:48.260
Words of encouragement, you mean. I see.

00:13:47.260 --> 00:13:48.260
Teio...

00:13:48.260 --> 00:13:49.000
Anything else?

00:14:02.800 --> 00:14:04.500
Palmer begins to fall behind!

00:14:04.500 --> 00:14:06.530
And then, from the outside, 
McQueen is moving up on the outside!

00:14:06.530 --> 00:14:08.390
And behind her is Ikuno Dictus!

00:14:08.390 --> 00:14:10.760
But McQueen, she's maintaining her lead!

00:14:10.760 --> 00:14:13.260
And she passes the goal while in first place!

00:14:12.260 --> 00:14:13.260
Takarazuka Kinen

00:14:12.260 --> 00:14:13.260
{\an2}Takarazuka Kinen

00:14:13.650 --> 00:14:16.140
Wow, McQueen was really amazing out there!

00:14:16.140 --> 00:14:20.340
Yes, this is her first victory at the 
Takarazuka Kinen. She's bound to be pleased.

00:14:21.260 --> 00:14:25.430
She was originally scheduled to 
 race against Tokai Teio.

00:14:25.780 --> 00:14:28.070
This is the third time she's 
broken her leg, right?

00:14:25.780 --> 00:14:31.530
MCQUEEN TAKES THE TAKARAZUKA!

00:14:28.070 --> 00:14:31.530
From what I hear, there's a good 
chance she may have to exit—

00:14:32.980 --> 00:14:35.100
I don't care what anyone else says.

00:14:35.540 --> 00:14:37.650
And there's no point in getting mopey.

00:14:45.040 --> 00:14:46.330
Teio-san?!

00:14:47.550 --> 00:14:49.750
Hey! Good to see you all again.

00:14:49.750 --> 00:14:52.550
McQueen, congrats on the Takarazuka Kinen!

00:14:52.550 --> 00:14:53.880
Teio...

00:14:53.880 --> 00:14:55.940
Are you seriously okay?

00:14:55.940 --> 00:14:59.630
I got released last week, 
but I've been bored out of my mind!

00:14:59.630 --> 00:15:01.200
So I came to watch you all train.

00:15:04.220 --> 00:15:06.780
What's wrong, Gold Ship?!

00:15:06.780 --> 00:15:10.720
The news wouldn't shut up about you 
not being able to make a comeback!

00:15:10.720 --> 00:15:12.820
So I'm just so happy!

00:15:13.450 --> 00:15:14.830
I'm okay!

00:15:14.830 --> 00:15:19.290
Trust me, you break your leg three times, 
and you start to get a feel for how bad it is.

00:15:19.290 --> 00:15:21.710
This is so great, Teio-san!

00:15:21.710 --> 00:15:25.010
If you need to do rehab, I've got 
your back! Anything you need!

00:15:25.770 --> 00:15:28.190
Continuing to race is something I can't—

00:15:30.590 --> 00:15:32.860
Yeah. Thanks, guys.

00:15:33.370 --> 00:15:34.760
So, that said...

00:15:35.000 --> 00:15:37.140
Sitting around is gonna just make me anxious,

00:15:37.510 --> 00:15:41.160
so starting today, I'll be supporting 
you all as team leader again!

00:15:37.510 --> 00:15:43.270
<font size="14">I am the leader</font>

00:15:41.160 --> 00:15:43.270
If you need any shopping done
or anything, let me know!

00:15:43.270 --> 00:15:44.830
Your reign only lasted a few days, huh?

00:15:44.830 --> 00:15:45.730
Shut it.

00:15:45.730 --> 00:15:47.470
You're sure that's all right?

00:15:47.470 --> 00:15:48.270
You bet!

00:15:48.270 --> 00:15:49.520
Leave it to me!

00:15:50.240 --> 00:15:52.240
S.S. Golshi #2

00:15:52.240 --> 00:15:56.370
Let's see, I got that, and that...

00:15:56.820 --> 00:16:00.860
So that leaves compresses, 
supplements, protein, and...

00:15:59.700 --> 00:16:01.490
Hey, it's Tokai Teio!

00:16:02.000 --> 00:16:03.140
Hello there.

00:16:03.140 --> 00:16:04.250
Hello there!

00:16:04.710 --> 00:16:06.180
Um, Teio-san...

00:16:07.170 --> 00:16:10.040
We used to root for you.

00:16:11.130 --> 00:16:13.110
You had a really great run.

00:16:13.110 --> 00:16:14.860
Thank you for everything.

00:16:14.860 --> 00:16:16.010
You too, Kanna.

00:16:16.010 --> 00:16:17.720
Good luck, Teio-san!

00:16:17.720 --> 00:16:19.260
Uh... Right.

00:16:19.260 --> 00:16:20.990
You'll have to excuse us.

00:16:20.990 --> 00:16:22.350
Bye-bye!

00:16:22.350 --> 00:16:23.520
Bye-bye.

00:16:26.830 --> 00:16:29.220
"Used to root for you," huh?

00:16:29.950 --> 00:16:32.290
Okay, back to shopping.

00:16:32.290 --> 00:16:34.820
Honey, honey, honey,

00:16:34.820 --> 00:16:35.760
honey...

00:16:38.240 --> 00:16:41.250
Sweets! Sweets! Sweets!

00:16:41.250 --> 00:16:59.810
Sweets! Sweets! Sweets!

00:16:59.810 --> 00:17:03.220
Why?! Why am I so slow?!

00:17:03.220 --> 00:17:06.230
Hurry it up! We're going on ahead!

00:17:06.230 --> 00:17:07.310
Wait up!

00:17:07.310 --> 00:17:08.480
Guys!

00:17:08.990 --> 00:17:10.610
Hey, listen!

00:17:10.610 --> 00:17:12.900
Don't leave me behind!

00:17:12.900 --> 00:17:14.940
Guys!

00:17:34.910 --> 00:17:39.930
Sweets, sweets, sweets...

00:17:37.960 --> 00:17:39.930
Is something wrong?

00:17:40.800 --> 00:17:42.180
Well, it's just...

00:17:42.890 --> 00:17:45.010
What do you think, McQueen?

00:17:53.850 --> 00:17:55.940
This is her third fracture.

00:17:55.940 --> 00:17:59.160
Do you think Teio will be able 
to run again like she used to?

00:18:00.920 --> 00:18:03.340
She believes she can.

00:18:04.350 --> 00:18:06.920
And I must simply believe in her.

00:18:07.710 --> 00:18:08.730
I see.

00:18:09.380 --> 00:18:15.090
You shouldn't be so hard on yourself. 
It's only going to make Teio more anxious.

00:18:15.640 --> 00:18:18.170
Right... sorry.

00:18:35.690 --> 00:18:38.420
Teio, you got a second?

00:18:38.420 --> 00:18:39.820
What's up?

00:18:40.170 --> 00:18:42.340
Well, y'know...

00:18:42.340 --> 00:18:45.270
And hey, when are you gonna 
have my comeback plan ready?

00:18:45.270 --> 00:18:46.960
I'm getting tired of waiting!

00:18:46.960 --> 00:18:49.830
Yeah, you're right. Sorry.

00:18:49.830 --> 00:18:52.120
Seriously, quit apologizing!

00:18:52.120 --> 00:18:54.330
Hey, there you are.

00:18:54.670 --> 00:18:55.540
Sup.

00:18:55.540 --> 00:18:57.410
What's up, guys? Did you go shopping?

00:18:57.410 --> 00:18:58.260
Yeah!

00:18:58.260 --> 00:19:01.040
Teio-san, this is perfect timing!

00:19:01.550 --> 00:19:03.930
Ta-dah! We're making you a nutrition drink!

00:19:05.690 --> 00:19:10.110
We were wondering if our special drink 
is what helped you bounce back last time.

00:19:10.110 --> 00:19:10.910
Right?

00:19:10.910 --> 00:19:12.810
Oh... you were?

00:19:12.810 --> 00:19:15.110
Please drink it so you'll feel better sooner!

00:19:15.110 --> 00:19:16.410
Let's see, first...

00:19:16.410 --> 00:19:19.660
It's gotta have milk, right? 
She needs her calcium!

00:19:19.660 --> 00:19:21.280
What about garlic, for stamina?

00:19:21.280 --> 00:19:23.050
That's still rejected from last time!

00:19:23.050 --> 00:19:25.150
Let's put some carrots in! They're delicious!

00:19:25.150 --> 00:19:26.260
How about dried sardines?

00:19:26.260 --> 00:19:28.730
We're not just putting 
in <i>anything</i> for calcium!

00:19:28.730 --> 00:19:30.140
Thanks, guys.

00:19:30.570 --> 00:19:33.370
I bet I'll be able to run again in no time.

00:19:35.130 --> 00:19:38.050
Maybe even faster than before!

00:19:38.050 --> 00:19:39.660
Hey, don't expect too much!

00:19:39.660 --> 00:19:40.910
Please get well soon!

00:19:40.910 --> 00:19:42.680
Yeah, hurry it up already!

00:19:51.920 --> 00:19:55.090
It's hard to say whether you'll ever be 
able to run in the same fashion again.

00:19:55.090 --> 00:19:57.830
There's a good chance she 
may have to exit the—

00:19:57.830 --> 00:20:00.710
Teio-san, we used to root for you.

00:20:11.070 --> 00:20:12.470
Oh, Teio.

00:20:12.470 --> 00:20:16.270
Hey, McQueen. Doing some late secret training?

00:20:16.270 --> 00:20:16.960
Yes.

00:20:16.960 --> 00:20:20.090
It'd be a sorry state of affairs 
if I wasn't prepared for when

00:20:20.090 --> 00:20:21.460
my rival returns to racing.

00:20:22.520 --> 00:20:23.400
Teio!

00:20:24.000 --> 00:20:26.250
Could you call my time?

00:20:27.430 --> 00:20:29.850
You sure you want your rival 
to have that kind of intel?

00:20:31.000 --> 00:20:34.850
Get a good look at how I run.

00:20:38.510 --> 00:20:40.660
I'll always be waiting up ahead.

00:20:46.550 --> 00:20:47.990
Waiting for you.

00:20:51.020 --> 00:20:52.150
Ready...

00:20:52.750 --> 00:20:53.600
Go!

00:21:40.970 --> 00:21:43.680
Wow... she's so fast.

00:21:45.470 --> 00:21:47.130
Like she's flying.

00:21:49.020 --> 00:21:50.800
It's so beautiful.

00:22:02.670 --> 00:22:05.390
I see. I get it now.

00:22:08.250 --> 00:22:10.860
Teio? How was that?

00:22:16.470 --> 00:22:17.770
I'm never...

00:22:18.540 --> 00:22:21.140
gonna be able to run like that again.

00:22:21.750 --> 00:22:24.990
What was that? I didn't hear you!

00:22:24.990 --> 00:22:26.510
What was my time?

00:22:26.770 --> 00:22:29.510
Teio! Say, Teio!

00:22:29.830 --> 00:22:33.080
What was my time?!

00:22:30.880 --> 00:22:33.500
I'm so sorry, McQueen.

00:22:33.500 --> 00:22:35.330
Teio, are you listening?

00:22:36.305 --> 00:23:36.214
